    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Giles R. Wright was an American clergyman.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The <emph render="bold">Giles R. Wright Papers</emph> is divided into three series.  <emph render="bold">Miscellaneous</emph> includes, among other things, a folder of programs of church services in which Wright participated as minister. <emph render="bold">Published material</emph> contains magazine articles and newspaper clippings primarily of a religious nature.  <emph render="bold">Writings</emph> contains notes and essays from Wright's college years as well as handwritten copies of his sermons and speeches as a minister.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
      <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
      <p>Material is arranged alphabetically by type within each series.</p>
    </arrangement>
